# Subpar Battery Implementation

You are adding a new structure type (Subpar Battery) to a vanilla JS browser game.

## Project Structure

- `game.js` — Single IIFE containing all game logic (~640 lines). All code lives here.
- `index.html` — Game page with sidebar UI (action buttons, tile info, log, hotkey modal)
- `style.css` — Mars-themed dark styling

## Conventions (MUST follow exactly)

- All JS is inside the IIFE `(function () { "use strict"; ... })()` in `game.js`
- Structures are stored in `state.structures` as `{ type: "type_name", row, col, ...extraProps }`
- Existing types: `"rock_hovel"` (has `energy` property), `"solar_panel"`
- Build functions follow pattern: `canBuildX()` returns boolean, `buildX()` does the action
- `getStructureAt(row, col)` finds a structure at a position
- `getAdjacentHovels(row, col)` finds adjacent Rock Hovels — use this pattern for new adjacency helpers
- `addLog(message, type)` for game log entries. Existing types: "move", "gather", "turn", "build", "energy"
- Canvas drawing: `drawStructure()` dispatches by `structure.type`. Each type has its own draw function.
- UI buttons: `<button id="..." class="action-btn" disabled>Label</button>` in `#action-panel`
- Hotkeys: switch/case block in the `keydown` listener. Existing: w/s/a/d=move, g=gather, b=hovel, p=solar, e/Enter=end turn, Escape=modal
- Button enable/disable logic is in `updateUI()`
- Tile info display is in `updateTileInfo()`
- `var` is used for some older code, but `const`/`let` are also used. Match whichever style is nearest to your insertion point.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Helper functions (add near `getAdjacentHovels`)

```js
function getAdjacentStructures(row, col, type) {
    var results = [];
    for (var dr = -1; dr <= 1; dr++) {
        for (var dc = -1; dc <= 1; dc++) {
            if (dr === 0 && dc === 0) continue;
            var nr = row + dr;
            var nc = col + dc;
            if (nr < 0 || nr >= MAP_ROWS || nc < 0 || nc >= MAP_COLS) continue;
            var s = getStructureAt(nr, nc);
            if (s && s.type === type) results.push(s);
        }
    }
    return results;
}
```

```js
function getHovelCapacity(hovel) {
    var base = 2;
    var seen = new Set(); // track battery positions to avoid double-counting
    // Direct adjacent batteries
    var directBatteries = getAdjacentStructures(hovel.row, hovel.col, "subpar_battery");
    for (var i = 0; i < directBatteries.length; i++) {
        seen.add(directBatteries[i].row + "," + directBatteries[i].col);
    }
    // Two-hop: batteries adjacent to Solar Panels that are adjacent to the hovel
    var adjacentPanels = getAdjacentStructures(hovel.row, hovel.col, "solar_panel");
    for (var p = 0; p < adjacentPanels.length; p++) {
        var panelBatteries = getAdjacentStructures(adjacentPanels[p].row, adjacentPanels[p].col, "subpar_battery");
        for (var b = 0; b < panelBatteries.length; b++) {
            seen.add(panelBatteries[b].row + "," + panelBatteries[b].col);
        }
    }
    return base + seen.size * 4;
}
```

### 2. Build functions (add near `buildSolarPanel`)

```js
function canBuildSubparBattery() {
    var unit = state.unit;
    if (state.resources.energy < 2 || state.resources.rocks < 2) return false;
    if (getStructureAt(unit.row, unit.col) !== null) return false;
    var adjPanels = getAdjacentStructures(unit.row, unit.col, "solar_panel");
    var adjHovels = getAdjacentStructures(unit.row, unit.col, "rock_hovel");
    return adjPanels.length > 0 || adjHovels.length > 0;
}

function buildSubparBattery() {
    if (!canBuildSubparBattery()) return;
    var unit = state.unit;
    state.resources.energy -= 2;
    state.resources.rocks -= 2;
    state.structures.push({
        type: "subpar_battery",
        row: unit.row,
        col: unit.col,
    });
    addLog("Elon built a Subpar Battery at (" + unit.col + ", " + unit.row + ")", "build");
    render();
    updateUI();
}
```

### 3. Explosion processing (add near `processSolarPanels`)

```js
function processSubparBatteryExplosions() {
    for (var i = state.structures.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var s = state.structures[i];
        if (s.type !== "subpar_battery") continue;
        if (Math.random() < 0.02) {
            addLog("A Subpar Battery at (" + s.col + ", " + s.row + ") exploded!", "explosion");
            state.structures.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}
```

Call `processSubparBatteryExplosions()` in `endTurn()` BEFORE `processSolarPanels()` so that exploded batteries don't contribute to capacity that turn.

### 4. Fix energy cap in `processSolarPanels()`

Change `if (hovels[j].energy < 2)` to `if (hovels[j].energy < getHovelCapacity(hovels[j]))`.

### 5. Canvas rendering (add near `drawSolarPanel`)

Create `drawSubparBattery(structure)` — draw a green/lime battery shape with terminal nubs and a "BATTERY" label. Use TILE_SIZE constant for positioning.

Update `drawStructure()` to dispatch: `if (structure.type === "subpar_battery") { drawSubparBattery(structure); return; }`

### 6. UI (index.html)

Add after the Solar Panel button in `#action-panel`:
```html
<button id="build-battery-btn" class="action-btn" disabled>Build Subpar Battery (2 ⚡ 2 🪨)</button>
```

Add hotkey row in the modal table tbody (after the Solar Panel row):
```html
<tr><td><kbd>T</kbd></td><td>Build Subpar Battery</td></tr>
```

### 7. UI logic (game.js)

In `updateUI()`, add:
```js
var batteryBtn = document.getElementById("build-battery-btn");
batteryBtn.disabled = !canBuildSubparBattery();
```

Add click listener:
```js
document.getElementById("build-battery-btn").addEventListener("click", buildSubparBattery);
```

In keyboard handler, add case `"t"` to call `buildSubparBattery()`.

### 8. Tile info (game.js `updateTileInfo()`)

Add `else if` for `subpar_battery` type → `structureText = "Subpar Battery"`.

For Rock Hovel, change `' / 2'` to `' / ' + getHovelCapacity(tileStructure)` so it reflects dynamic capacity.

### 9. CSS (style.css)

Add log entry style for explosions:
```css
#game-log .log-entry.explosion {
    color: #ff4444;
}
```

## Gotchas

- Iterate structures in REVERSE when removing (explosion) to avoid index shifting bugs.
- The `getHovelCapacity()` must deduplicate batteries reachable both directly and via Solar Panel (use a Set keyed on row,col).
- The `processSolarPanels()` hardcoded `energy < 2` MUST be replaced with `energy < getHovelCapacity(hovels[j])` — this is the core integration point.
- `state.resources.energy` tracks total energy across all hovels. When a hovel stores more due to increased cap, `state.resources.energy` still increments normally in `processSolarPanels()`.
- Button click listener must be added OUTSIDE the IIFE's function definitions, near the existing `addEventListener` calls at the bottom.
